Research along all these lines can help to reduce hallucinations and bias in LLM responses -- particularly in the context of long-tail and multi-hop factual questions -- but must address the challenges posed by the patchy and incomplete nature of KGs, and the need to reliably disambiguate which KG entities are mentioned in a text.